una, Uppsala, Sweden","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Greger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Gregory</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gregers","meanings":["Via Latin <i>Gregorius</i> from the post-classical Greek name <i>Gregōrios</i> ‘watchful’ (a derivative of <i>gregōrein</i> ‘to watch, be vigilant’). The name was a very popular one among the early Christians, who were mindful of the injunction ‘be sober, be vigilant’ (1 Peter 5:8). It was borne by a number of early saints. The most important, in honour of whom the name was often bestowed from medieval times onwards, were Gregory of Nazianzen (  <i>c.</i>329–90 ), Gregory of Nyssa (  d. <i>c.</i>395 ), Gregory of Tours (  538–94 ), and  Pope Gregory the Great  (  <i>c.</i>540–604 ). A famous bearer of the name in modern times is the film star  Gregory Peck  (  1916–2003 ). The name has traditionally been popular in Scotland, where it is often found in the form  <b>Gregor</b> ."]},{"name":"Gregory","meanings":["Via Latin <i>Gregorius</i> from the post-classical Greek name <i>Gregōrios</i> ‘watchful’ (a derivative of <i>gregōrein</i> ‘to watch, be vigilant’). The name was a very popular one among the early Christians, who were mindful of the injunction ‘be sober, be vigilant’ (1 Peter 5:8). It was borne by a number of early saints. The most important, in honour of whom the name was often bestowed from medieval times onwards, were Gregory of Nazianzen (  <i>c.</i>329–90 ), Gregory of Nyssa (  d. <i>c.</i>395 ), Gregory of Tours (  538–94 ), and  Pope Gregory the Great  (  <i>c.</i>540–604 ). A famous bearer of the name in modern times is the film star  Gregory Peck  (  1916–2003 ). The name has traditionally been popular in Scotland, where it is often found in the form  <b>Gregor</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1702076,"age":19,"year":"1436","julianDay":2245548,"title":"The Engelbrekt Rebellion","description":"Engelb